[In the northern hemisphere, seasonal influenza is lingering longer than in previous years, but no drastically different antigenic strains have appeared, nor has there been any increase in the number of isolates with enhanced resistance to the neuraminidase inhibiters currently in use. However, the vaccine being produced now to combat the expected seasonal viruses in the northern hemisphere has been amended slightly to take account of minor changes in the current A/H3N2 virus component. - Mod.CP]
